name: 10 Must-Try Mexican Recipes You've Been Missing Out On
The Best of Mexico's Oaxacan Cuisine
Crispy Turkey Flautas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cooked, shredded turkey'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green onions'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '24', 'unit': '', 'name': 'small white corn tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg white to seal flautas (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded napa cabbage'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'guacamole'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}
steps: Mix shredded turkey, pepper Jack cheese, green onions, salt and pepper together in a bowl.. Wrap stack of tortillas in a paper towel and place in a sealable plastic bag. Seal the bag only halfway. Microwave on high until tortillas are hot and flexible, about 45 seconds. Keep tortillas warm in the bag as you fill the others.. Place 2 tortillas on a work surface, one about 2 inches off center of the first creating a longer partially double tortilla. Spoon about 1/4 to 1/3 cup turkey mixture in a row just below the center of the long side of the tortilla. Paint a bit of egg white along the top edge of the tortillas. Bring bottom edge of the tortilla up and over the filling and roll rather tightly toward the top edge over the egg white. Set aside with the fold on the bottom while you fill the remaining tortillas.. Place 1/4 inch vegetable oil in a saute pan over medium heat. When oil is hot, place flautas in oil, seam side down. Press down gently with a spatula a couple of seconds to flatten bottoms. Fry in batches until flautas are crispy, golden, and heated through, 3 to 4 minutes per side. Drain about a minute on paper towels. Serve topped with shredded cabbage, guacamole, sour cream, salsa, and chopped cilantro.

name: Chicken Adobo Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'bay leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'granulated garlic'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'avocado oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'mango'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'oma tomato'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper,'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}
steps: Combine soy sauce, vinegar, bay leaves, and garlic in a large plastic bag with a zipper. Gently squeeze to mix well. Add chicken and coat with marinade. Squeeze out as much air from the bag as possible, coat all the chicken pieces with marinade, seal, and refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, combine vinegar, fish sauce, avocado oil, sugar, and black pepper in a bowl for the salsa. Stir with a whisk or fork until sugar is dissolved. Add mango, tomato, red onion, jalapeño, and chopped cilantro to the bowl. Toss to combine, and refrigerate salsa until ready to serve.. For tacos, remove chicken pieces from the marinade and reserve the marinade.. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Carefully add the chicken thighs, and brown on each side, 1 to 2 minutes, then remove chicken to a plate.. To the same skillet, add onion, and cook for about 1 minute. Stir in minced garlic and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add reserved marinade, water, brown sugar, and black pepper, and bring to a boil.. Return chicken to the skillet, smooth side down. Reduce heat to low, and simmer chicken uncovered, about 15 minutes. The liquid should bubble gently. Turn chicken and simmer 10 minutes more. Remove chicken from skillet to rest.. Cook sauce over medium heat until syrupy, thick, and reduced, about 10 minutes. Remove skillet from heat. Remove bay leaves and discard.. Slice chicken into 1/2-inch slices and return to the skillet to coat in the sauce. Garnish with fresh cilantro and chopped green onions, if desired.. Fill each tortilla with chicken strips and top with mango salsa. Serve immediately.

name: Roscoe's Chilaquiles
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chile peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chile pepper,'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'Roma tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'white onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'beef bouillon cube'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'culantro leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': None, 'name': 'corn tortillas'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Mexican crema'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'otija cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado,'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano,'}
steps: For salsa roja, pour boiling water over peppers and let sit until softened, 15 to 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, add 2 tablespoons olive oil to a skillet over high heat, and sear tomatoes, onions, and garlic until charred for about 2 minutes.. Place softened peppers, charred vegetables, and 1 cup of the chile soaking water in a blender. Reserve remaining 3 cups chile water.  Blend until smooth. Strain the sauce; pour back into the pan.. Cook sauce over medium heat, scraping any charred bits from the bottom of the pan; add 2 cups of remaining chile water. Simmer until sauce is reduced by 1/3. Stir in bouillon cube and last 1 cup chile water, culantro leaves, lime juice; stir until bouillon cube dissolves. Season with salt and pepper.. For chilaquiles, heat oil to 350 degrees F ( 175 degrees C) in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add tortillas and fry until crisp and golden. 2 minutes per batch.. For each serving, heat 1 tablespoon oil in a small nonstick pan over medium heat. Crack an egg into the skillet, and cook until outer edges become opaque, about 1 minute. Turn egg over and cook until whites are completely opaque, 1 to 2 minutes more.. Add a handful of chips to the salsa roja, and turn to coat completely. Remove to a serving plate with a slotted spoon.. Drizzle with crema, top with an egg, cotija cheese, avocado, cilantro, squeeze of lime juice, and drizzle with more salsa roja. Sprinkle with oregano. Repeat with remaining ingredients.

name: Taquito Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(19 ounce) can', 'name': 'enchilada sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen corn'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8.8 ounce) package', 'name': 'white rice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'taco seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend, divided'}, {'quantity': '20', 'unit': None, 'name': 'beef and cheese flour tortilla taquitos'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pickling liquid from jarred pickled jalapenos'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pickled jalapenos'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro leaves'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly coat a 9x13-inch baking dish with cooking spray; set aside.. Stir together enchilada sauce, beans, corn, rice, bell pepper, red onion, cream, taco seasoning, salt, paprika, cumin, and 3 cups shredded cheese in a large bowl until well combined.. Spread into the prepared baking dish in an even layer. Arrange taquitos evenly over rice mixture.. Bake in the preheated oven until taquitos are crispy and rice mixture is bubbling, about 40 minutes.. Meanwhile, whisk together sour cream, lime juice, and pickling liquid in a small bowl until smooth. Set aside, uncovered, at room temperature until ready to serve.. Remove baking dish from oven, and sprinkle evenly with remaining cheese. Top evenly with jalapeño slices. Bake at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) until cheese is melted, about 8 minutes more.. Let stand for 10 minutes. Top evenly with cilantro leaves. Drizzle each serving with jalapeño crema.

name: Rajas con Crema (Roasted Poblano Peppers in Cream Sauce)
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'poblano peppers'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Mexican crema'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chicken bouillon granules'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Oaxaca cheese'}
steps: Place poblano chiles directly on the grates of a gas stove. Cook over medium heat, flipping with tongs occasionally, until blackened and charred, about 5 minutes. Place in a sealed plastic bag and allow to cool, 5 to 6 minutes. Peel off charred skins, remove seeds, and slice chiles into strips. Set aside.. Melt butter in a large skillet. Add onions and cook until soft and translucent, 6 to 7 minutes. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add poblano peppers, Mexican crema, salt, chicken bouillon, and pepper; cook and stir until combined. Turn off heat, add cheese, and stir until melted.

name: Arroz Verde with Hatch Chiles
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green chiles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'long grain rice'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chicken bouillon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}
steps: Place Hatch chiles directly on the grates of a gas stove. Cook over medium heat, flipping with tongs occasionally, until blackened and charred, about 5 minutes. Place in a sealed plastic bag and allow to cool, 7 to 8 minutes.. Peel off charred skins; remove seeds. Place chiles, chicken broth and cilantro in the jar of a blender and blend until smooth. Set aside.. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat until it shimmers; add rice and onion. Cook and stir until lightly browned, about 2 minutes. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in chicken bouillon, salt, and cumin. Add chile mixture and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer until rice is tender, 25 to 30 minutes.

name: Chicken Fajita Skillet Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'poblano peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'orange bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'white onion'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes and green chiles'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'rotisserie chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce)', 'name': 'can pinto beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'lettuce'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Heat oil in a large, oven proof skillet over medium-high heat. Add peppers and onions and cook, undisturbed, 5 minutes or until browned. Add chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, salt and pepper and continue cooking until vegetables are soft, stirring often, 1 to 2  minutes. Remove vegetables from the pan and set aside.. Add butter to the pan and melt over moderate heat. Whisk in flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add in tomatoes and broth and cook until thick and creamy, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes. Stir in chicken and beans. Top chicken mixture with 1 cup cheese. Spread reserved peppers and onions evenly over the cheese and top with chips and remaining cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven until bubbly and lightly browned on top, about 15  minutes. Serve with desired toppings.

name: Beef Birria Queso Tacos with Consommé
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'reserved sauce from beef birria recipe'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced carrots'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced celery'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced cabbage'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'reserved beef fat from beef birria recipe, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(5 inch)', 'name': 'corn tortillas'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'freshly grated Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Beef Birria'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped white onion, or to taste, divided'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro, or to taste, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'lime, cut into 4 wedges'}
steps: To make the consommé: Stir beef birria sauce, chicken broth, carrots, celery, and cabbage together in a saucepan over high heat. Bring to a simmer, then reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer, occasionally brushing the caramelized bits (fond) off the side with the hot liquid, until vegetables are nice and tender and consommé has reached the desired consistency, about 20 minutes. Reduce the heat to low and keep hot while you prepare the tacos.. To make the tacos: Heat some reserved beef fat in a large skillet over medium heat until melted. Add two tortillas and flip with a spatula until generously coated in fat. Toast briefly until golden brown, then cover with Monterey Jack cheese and some shredded beef. Drizzle each taco with about 1 tablespoon consommé liquid, then top with some white onion and cilantro.. Fold tacos in half and press gently. Continue to cook, flipping back and forth, until browned and crispy, 2 to 3 minutes. Transfer to a plate and repeat to make remaining tacos, adding more fat if necessary.. Ladle consommé into a bowl and garnish with any remaining white onion and cilantro. Squeeze lime wedges into consommé and serve with tacos.

name: Chicken Chalupas
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'iceberg lettuce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'pico de gallo'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'refried beans'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'taco seasoning'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'oil for frying'}
steps: To make the chalupa shells, combine flour, baking powder, and salt in a medium mixing bowl. Stir well to combine the dry ingredients.. Gradually pour in milk, while stirring, until you need to use your hand to knead. Add in the melted butter, and knead well.. Shape dough into 6 equal balls. Sprinkle flour over a work surface and flour the rolling pin. Roll each dough ball into about a 7-inch circle, moving the dough a quarter turn after a couple of passes with the rolling pin. Add more flour to the work surface and rolling pin if dough sticks.. Keep rolled dough circles under a clean, damp kitchen towel until ready to fry.. Set up stations of chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes, shredded cheese, and any optional toppings you plan to use, and place in a convenient array for assembling the chalupas.. Microwave refried beans on medium setting until soft and spreadable, about 1 minute, and add as the first station to your other ingredients.. Warm shredded chicken briefly in the microwave or in a skillet, and toss with taco seasoning mix, and add as the second station to the other ingredients.. To fry chalupa shells, add cooking oil to a depth of about 1/4-inch to a large, nonstick skillet. Heat oil over medium heat, and when the oil is hot, fry one side of one dough circle until lightly brown, about 1 minute.Using tongs, lift the partially cooked shell from the skillet and place only half of the uncooked side into the oil. Carefully hold half of the shell away from the oil, until the first half is browned, about 1 minute, then brown the other half. Repeat until all the shells are done.. To keep the bent shape, place fried chalupa shells into a taco holder until ready to fill.. To serve, spread each chalupa shell with about 2 tablespoons refried beans, and fill with 2 or 3 tablespoons seasoned shredded chicken. Fill with lettuce, tomatoes, and cheese.. Garnish with optional toppings, such as pico de gallo, sour cream, and sliced avocados, if desired. Serve immediately.

name: Chilaquiles Breakfast Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(20 ounce) can', 'name': 'enchilada sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tomato salsa'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green chilies'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'thick-cut tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'queso fresco cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro leaves'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sour cream (optional)'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'hot sauce (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Add enchilada sauce, salsa, Hatch chilies, lime juice, chili powder, cumin, oregano, and green onions to a bowl and whisk thoroughly.. Toss Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheeses together; set aside.. Transfer 1 ladle of sauce into the bottom of a 9x12-inch baking dish. Top with half the chips, arranging into an even layer. Ladle over half the remaining sauce. Top evenly with half the cheese mixture.. Top with remaining chips, arranging into an even layer. Ladle over remaining sauce. Top evenly with the remaining cheese mixture.. Bake in the preheated oven until the casserole is heated through and cheese is starting to brown, 20 to 25 minutes.. In the last few minutes of baking time, prepare the eggs by frying or poaching, or bake them on top of the casserole as shown in the video. See Chef's Note for directions.. Serve casserole hot, topped with avocado, queso fresco, cilantro, sour cream, and hot sauce. Add a fried or poached egg to the top of each serving.

name: Creamy Mississippi Chicken Enchiladas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'dry ranch dressing mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pepperoncini peppers'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pepper juice'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(10 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sliced green onions'}
steps: Place chicken, ranch dressing mix, pepperoncini, pepper juice, butter, and water, in that order, into a slow cooker. Cook on High for 2 hours or Low for 3 1/2 hours until chicken easily shreds with a fork.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (1 degrees C). Remove half of the liquid in the slow cooker and discard. Shred chicken in the remaining liquid. Stir in cream cheese and sour cream.. Place about 1/2 cup chicken mixture and 2 tablespoons cheese in each tortilla and roll to seal. Place seam side down in a 9x13-inch casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese and pour heavy cream evenly over the top.. Bake in the preheated oven until browned around the edges and bubbly, about 30 minutes. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Top with green onions and pico de gallo.

name: Beef Enchilada Bake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'bell pepper, any color, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'chili beans'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'enchilada sauce, divided'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': None, 'name': 'corn tortillas'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'exican blend shredded cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cilantro, for garnish (optional)'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sour cream, for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Add olive oil, then add onions. Sauté until onions just start to soften, 2 to 3 minutes. Add bell pepper; sauté 1 to 2 minutes. Add garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 1 minute.. Add ground beef; cook, breaking up beef with a spatula, until browned and crumbly, about 10 minutes. Drain any grease. Stir in chili beans. Season with salt, black pepper, and cumin. Stir in 1 cup enchilada sauce, reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.. Meanwhile, spread remaining enchilada sauce evenly in the bottom of a 10x8-inch baking dish.. Using a sharp knife, carefully cut a straight edge off one side of the tortillas. Place 4 tortillas with the cut edge facing the sides of the dish.. Spread half of the beef mixture over tortillas and top with 3 ounces cheese. Add another layer of tortillas, then beef mixture and 3 ounces cheese to create the second layer. Repeat layers ending with remaining cheese. Cover with foil.. Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Remove foil; bake until cheese is lightly browned, 5 to 10 minutes more. Remove from the oven; allow to rest for 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Garnish with sour cream and chopped cilantro if desired.

name: Strawberry Tres Leches Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'baking spray'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'granulated sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole milk, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'strawberries, hulled and quartered, plus sliced strawberries for garnish'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'granulated sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12-ounce) can', 'name': 'evaporated milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14-ounce) can', 'name': 'sweetened condensed milk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'whipped topping to taste'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly spray a 13- x 9-inch baking dish with baking spray; set aside.. Whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt in a bowl. In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, beat eggs, sugar, and vanilla on medium speed until light, fluffy, and almost doubled in volume, about 10 minutes.. Beat in half of the flour mixture on low speed until just incorporated. Gradually stream in the milk until combined, followed by the remaining flour mixture. Transfer batter to prepared baking dish.. Bake in preheated oven until golden brown and a wooden skewer inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and allow to cool on a wire rack in the pan for 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, for the strawberry milk toss strawberries and sugar in a small bowl until fully coated, let rest at room temperature for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Transfer to a blender and process until smooth, about 30 seconds. Strain puree through a fine mesh sieve into a large bowl, discarding any pulp or seeds. Whisk together 1 cup of the strained strawberry puree (reserving any remaining for a later use), evaporated milk, condensed milk, and heavy cream into a large bowl until fullycombined.. Using a wooden skewer or the tines of a fork, poke holes all over the top of the cooled Cake, pour strawberry ,ilk mixture evenly over cake. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or up to 12 hours.. Top with a layer of whipped topping and sliced strawberries before serving.

name: Black Bean Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'nonstick cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped white onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'minced, seeded jalapeño'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(15 ounce) cans', 'name': 'black beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'jarred medium picante sauce or chunky salsa (such as Pace)'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'sweet whole kernel corn, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped, seeded tomato'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Monterey Jack cheese, shredded'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Cheddar cheese, shredded'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'thinly sliced green onions'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime wedges, cilantro leaves, sour cream, salsa, warm corn or flour tortillas, or tortilla chips, for serving'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Coat an 8x8-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion, bell pepper, and jalapeño; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and slightly browned, 5 to 7 minutes.. Stir in beans, picante sauce, water, salt, cumin, cayenne pepper, and smoked paprika. Mash beans using the back of a spoon or a potato masher until mixture is slightly thickened. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Simmer, undisturbed, until sauce thickens and bubbles appear all over the surface, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in corn.. Transfer mixture to the prepared baking dish, and sprinkle with tomato, Monterey Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese. Cover with aluminum foil.. Bake in the preheated oven until casserole is hot and cheeses are melted, 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with green onions. Let cool slightly before serving.. Serve with lime wedges, cilantro, sour cream, salsa, warm tortillas, or tortilla chips, if desired. Enjoy!

name: Air Fryer Chicken Quesadillas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'grated cheese (see Note)'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': None, 'name': 'wooden toothpicks'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'olive oil cooking spray'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C), according to manufacturer’s guidelines. Toss chicken with chili powder, cumin, and cayenne in a bowl.. Place a tortilla on a work surface and cover half the tortilla with about 2 tablespoons grated cheese. Top with 2 tablespoons chicken mixture, then top with 2 additional tablespoons grated cheese.. Fold tortilla in half and use wooden picks to hold the tortilla halves together. Spray both sides of the filled tortilla with olive oil spray.. Air fry quesadillas in a single layer until tortillas are lightly browned and cheese is melted, about 4 minutes per side. You may have to cook in batches. Serve warm with your favorite toppings.

name: Trout Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '16', 'unit': None, 'name': 'white corn tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'purple cabbage'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'coleslaw mix'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Mexican crema'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lime zest'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime wedges as needed, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cilantro leaves'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'filets', 'name': 'trout'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon', 'name': 'tapioca starch'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chipotle powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Mexican oregano'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'prepared guacamole, or as needed'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Wrap tortillas in foil.. Bake tortillas in the preheated oven until warm, 8 to 10 minutes.. Meanwhile, place cabbage, white parts of green onion, coleslaw mix, 3 tablespoons Mexican crema, lime zest, juice of 2 lime wedges, and cilantro in a large bowl. Toss to coat; season with salt and pepper. Set aside... Carefully remove skin from trout. Cut each trout filet into 2- to 3-inch pieces. Stir tapioca starch, cumin, chipotle powder, and Mexican oregano together in a shallow bowl.. Dip fish pieces into seasoning mixture to coat.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add coated fish pieces; cook until golden brown and fish flakes easily with a fork, 2 to 3 minutes per side. Transfer to a drip tray, and season with salt.. Using 2 corn tortillas for each taco, divide fish, slaw, and guacamole between the tacos. Garnish each with green tops of scallions. Serve with remaining lime wedges and crema on the side. Enjoy!

name: Air Fryer Quesadillas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'nonstick cooking spray'}
steps: Heat tortillas in the microwave until pliable, about 15 seconds.. Place 1/4 cup cheese on one half of each tortilla; fold other half of tortilla over cheese. Place in  air fryer. Spray with non-stick cooking spray.. Set temperature to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Place quesadillas in the basket of the air fryer, and cook until golden brown, 4 to 6 minutes. Flip quesadillas, press down with a spatula, and air fry an additional 2 to 3 minutes.

name: Pork Chile Verde
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'fresh tomatillos, or more to taste, husks removed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'serrano peppers'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, peeled'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lard or vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'pork shoulder, or more to taste, trimmed and cut into 1 ½-inch cubes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'yellow onion, coarsely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, coarsely chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red wine'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Combine tomatillos, serrano peppers, and garlic in a bowl. Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Transfer to a baking sheet.. Place in the preheated oven and roast until tender, about 30 minutes. Remove vegetables from oven, cool slightly, and transfer to the bowl of a food processor. Puree until smooth. Reduce oven temperature to 275 degrees F (135 degrees C).. While vegetables are roasting, heat lard in a Dutch oven or heavy oven-safe pot over medium-high heat. Sprinkle pork with garlic salt and pepper and add to the pot in batches. Cook each batch until browned, about 7 minutes, removing to a plate with a slotted spoon. Drain and discard all but 2 tablespoons pan drippings.. Add onion and bell pepper to the pot. Sauté, stirring occasionally, until onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes. Pour wine into the pan and bring to a boil while scraping the browned bits of food off the bottom of the pan with a wooden spoon. Stir in browned pork, tomatillo puree, chicken stock, cilantro, oregano, cumin, and salt.. Cover and cook in the oven until pork is tender, 3 ½ to 4 hours. Allow to stand for 15 minutes, covered, before serving.

name: Sheet Pan Quesadillas

name: Black Bean and Corn Quesadillas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'finely chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole kernel corn, drained'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Monterey Jack cheese'}
steps: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook and stir onion in hot oil until softened, about 2 minutes. Stir in beans and corn, then add salsa, brown sugar, and red pepper flakes; mix well. Cook until heated through, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat.. Melt about 1 ½ teaspoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Place a tortilla in the skillet. Sprinkle with ¼ of the Monterey Jack cheese, then top with ¼ of the bean mixture. Place another tortilla on top; cook until the bottom is golden, then carefully flip and cook until the other side is golden. Repeat with remaining tortillas and filling.

name: Simply Guacamole
ingredients: {'quantity': '5', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocados - peeled, pitted, and mashed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced green onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper, to taste'}
steps: Stir together the avocado and lemon juice in a serving bowl; add the green onion and cilantro; mix well. Season with salt and pepper. Serve immediately or store covered in refrigerator with avocado pits in the bowl to keep from browning.

name: Microwave Mexican Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'instant rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'picante sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4 ounce) can', 'name': 'green chiles'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': '(1 ounce) envelope', 'name': 'taco seasoning'}
steps: Place minute rice, water, picante sauce, green chiles, and taco seasoning in a large microwave-safe baking dish. Stir until evenly combined.. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 8 minutes. Let sit for 5 minutes to absorb liquid. Fluff with a fork and serve.

name: The Best Chimichangas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'plus 3 tablespoons water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chicken bouillon cube'}, {'quantity': '1 (7', 'unit': 'ounce) can', 'name': 'green chiles'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'peanut oil or vegetable oil for frying, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(10 to 12-inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'refried beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) block', 'name': 'pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'shredded lettuce'}
steps: Sprinkle salt, pepper, and garlic powder evenly over one side of the chicken breasts.. Heat olive oil in a large deep skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken, seasoned side down, into skillet, and cook, undisturbed, until browned, 3 to 4 minutes. Flip chicken over and push to one side of the pan.. Add onion, garlic, chili powder, and cumin to the skillet and cook for 1 minute.  Add 2 cups water and bouillon and gently stir until well combined.. Bring mixture to a simmer. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer gently until chicken is no longer pink at the center and juices run clear, about 20 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the center should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Remove chicken from pan and increase heat to medium-high; cook until broth mixture is reduced by about half. Shred chicken and add back to the pan, along with green chiles. Stir until well combined and remove from heat.. Whisk flour and remaining water together in a small bowl until smooth; set aside. Heat oil for frying in a large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium-high heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Set a wire rack over a rimmed baking sheet.. Place tortilla on work surface and spread about 3 tablespoons beans in the center. Top with 1/4 cup shredded cheese and 1/3 to 1/2 cup well-drained shredded chicken. Brush flour mixture lightly around edges of top half of tortilla. Fold sides of tortilla in just over edges of filling and fold bottom of tortilla up over filling.  Press back on the tortilla to push the filling tightly together and continue to roll upwards. Lightly press the edges of the tortilla to seal tightly and set aside, seam side down. Repeat with remaining ingredients.. Carefully place 2 burritos into hot oil and cook, turning occasionally, until golden brown and toasted on the outside, about 2 minutes. Drain on the prepared baking sheet. Bring oil back up to temperature and repeat with remaining burritos.. Top as desired with warm queso, pico de gallo, cilantro and shredded lettuce, or other toppings, and serve immediately.

name: Blackened Shrimp Tacos with Pineapple
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh pineapple'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onions'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'shrimp'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}
steps: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat; lightly oil the grate. Combine paprika, onion powder, oregano, cayenne pepper, garlic salt, and black pepper in a small bowl; set aside.. Cut the pineapple lengthwise into wedges. Grill pineapple wedges for 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Chop pineapple and combine in a bowl with red onions, cilantro, fresh lime juice, and salt.. Thread shrimp onto skewers; brush with melted butter, and coat with seasoning mix. Grill shrimp until they are bright pink on the outside and the meat is opaque, about 3 minutes per side.. Place tortillas on the hot grill and heat until lightly grilled, 20 to 30 seconds per side.. Place shrimp on each tortilla and top with pineapple mixture.

name: Pork Chops Al Pastor
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(12 to 14 ounce) bone-in double-cut p', 'name': 'bone-in double-cut p'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': '14 ounce)', 'name': 'pineapple chunks with juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili pepper, or any dried ground chile pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chipotle'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '3 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, peeled'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions, cut into 2-inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil, plus more as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'yellow onion, halved and sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water or chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'yellow onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh or canned pineapple'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh oregano leaves'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, juiced, or to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cayenne for garnish'}
steps: Place chops in a resealable plastic bag set in a bowl. Add pineapple, guajillo, New Mexico chili powder, chipotle, cinnamon, salt, white vinegar, garlic, and onions to the jar of a blender, and blend until marinade is smooth; pour marinade into bag. Massage pork to coat evenly. Press out air, seal the bag, and refrigerate overnight, or up to 48 hours.. Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C).. Heat olive oil in an oven-safe pan over medium-high heat. Remove chops from marinade, scraping off as much excess as possible; reserve all marinade for the sauce. Sear chops in the hot pan on both sides until lightly browned, about 3 minutes per side. Remove to a plate; set aside.. Add yellow onion, cumin, and dried oregano to the pan, and cook, stirring, for 1 minute. If pan seems dry, add another drizzle of oil.. Turn off heat, and pour in water. Stir, scraping any brown bits off the bottom of the pan. Place chops on top of onion mixture.. Roast in the preheated oven until pork is cooked to taste, 20 to 30 minutes, basting or brushing chops with pan juices occasionally. An internal temperature of 140 to 145 degrees F (60 to 63 degrees C) will ensure juicy, tender meat. Roasting time will vary greatly depending on size of chops, so check temperature with an instant-read thermometer early and often.. Meanwhile, pour marinade into a saucepan, and add about 1/2 cup of water, or as needed to achieve desired thickness. Bring to a simmer on medium-high heat, whisking occasionally. Taste sauce for seasoning; keep warm until needed.. To make salsa, combine white onion, diced pineapple, fresh oregano, ¼ teaspoon salt, and lime juice in a bowl and mix thoroughly.. Remove pork from the oven; tent with foil and let rest for 5 to 10 minutes before serving. While resting, tops of chops can be garnished with sauce and a spoon of salsa.

name: Cafe de Olla
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'grated piloncillo'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'stick', 'name': 'cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coffee'}
steps: Place water, piloncillo, and cinnamon in a pot. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer for 8 minutes.. Remove from heat, add coffee, and stir well. Cover pot and steep for 5 minutes. Pour through a fine mesh strainer twice or until free of any coffee granules.

name: Cornbread Taco Bake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'taco seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1 (10', 'unit': 'ounce)', 'name': 'tomatoes with green chilies'}, {'quantity': '1 (8.75', 'unit': 'ounce) can', 'name': 'corn, drained'}, {'quantity': '1 (15.5', 'unit': 'ounce) can', 'name': 'chili beans'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'heddar cheese, shredded'}, {'quantity': '1 (8.5', 'unit': 'ounce)', 'name': 'cornbread mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sour cream'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. In a deep cast iron skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink, breaking it into crumbles, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain off excess grease. Stir in taco seasoning, tomatoes with green chilies, corn, and chili beans. Stir in Cheddar cheese.. Stir cornbread mix, egg, and milk together in a bowl. Spread batter over beef mixture.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted near the center of cornbread comes out clean, about 25 minutes. Garnish each serving with sour cream and chopped green onions. Serve immediately.

name: Blackened Shrimp Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 (14', 'unit': 'ounce) bag classic', 'name': 'coleslaw mix'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapeno'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'limes, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'raw shrimp'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': None, 'name': 'flour tortillas, warmed'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'guacamole'}
steps: Place coleslaw mix, red onion. cilantro, jalapeno, lime juice, 1 tablespoon olive oil, salt, and cayenne pepper in a large bowl. Stir until evenly combined. Set aside.. In a separate bowl combine shrimp, blackened seasoning, and the remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons olive oil. Stir until evenly combined.. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add shrimp mixture and cook until shrimp are bright pink on the outside and the meat is opaque, about 6 minutes, stirring halfway through.. Divide coleslaw and shrimp between the tortillas. Top each taco with a dollop of guacamole.

name: What Is Birria and How Do You Make It?
Potato Soup with Chorizo
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '9 ounce', 'name': 'Mexican chorizo'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onions'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, pressed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chicken bouillon granules ('}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Combine chorizo and onions in a soup pot over medium heat and cook until onions are soft and translucent and chorizo is fully cooked, 7 to 8 minutes. Bring to a boil and simmer until potatoes are fork tender, 6 to 10 minutes. Reduce heat and stir in heavy whipping cream. Season with salt and pepper.

name: Te de Canela (Cinnamon Tea)
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'sticks', 'name': 'cinnamon, broken into pieces'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sweetener, such as honey, sugar, or piloncillo (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice, or as needed (optional)'}
steps: Place water and cinnamon sticks in a pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Strain tea and pour into a cup; add sweetener and lemon juice as desired.

name: Mexican Street Corn Deviled Eggs
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'dip'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'lime juice, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'cotija cheese, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Tajin® Clásico Seasoning'}
steps: Place eggs in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil, remove from heat, and let eggs stand in hot water for 15 minutes. Remove eggs from hot water, cool under cold running water, and peel. Cut eggs in half lengthwise.. Remove yolks to a small mixing bowl; mash with a fork. Add in Mexican street corn dip, mayonnaise, and lime juice. Stir together with a fork until fairly smooth; stir in 2 teaspoons of cotija cheese.. Fit a piping bag with a coupler and a tip with a fairly large opening. Drop piping bag into a tall glass and fold edges down around the glass. Spoon egg yolk filling into the bag. Gather edges and twist together. Pipe filling into egg whites. Alternately, spoon filling into a resealable plastic bag, press to remove excess air, and reseal. Cut one corner of bag off, and pipe filling into egg whites. Or, simply spoon filling into egg whites.. Sprinkle remaining cotija cheese over eggs; scatter on onion slivers and cilantro. Sprinkle with Tajin® seasoning and serve.

steps: Add soy sauce, mirin, sake, garlic, brown sugar, ginger, and Thai chili to the jar of a blender. Blend on high until smooth. Reserve 2 tablespoons marinade; pour remaining marinade into a resealable plastic bag.. Add steak to the resealable bag, close the bag, and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes or up to overnight.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Remove steak from the marinade,  shake off excess, and cook and stir steak in the skillet until browned, about 5 minutes. Discard the remaining marinade.. Meanwhile add broccoli to a microwave-safe steamer, and steam in the microwave until tender, about 3 minutes. Roughly chop the broccoli.. Remove steak to a plate to keep warm, and drizzle with the 2 tablespoons reserved marinade. Rinse the skillet and dry with a paper towel. Press down with a spatula, and cook until tortilla begins to brown and cheese melts, about 3 minutes. Carefully turn quesadilla over; cook until browned on the other side, about 3 minutes more. Repeat with remaining ingredients.. Cut quesadillas into wedges. Sprinkle with black sesame seeds and green onions; serve with Yum Yum sauce and teriyaki sauce, if desired.

name: Fried Egg Tortilla
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'taco seasoning, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 to 7-inch)', 'name': 'flour tortilla'}
steps: In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, melt butter over medium heat, and swirl the pan to coat the bottom evenly.. Carefully break egg into buttered skillet and cook until egg white is opaque and egg is firm enough to turn, about 1 minute.. name: Skillet Shrimp Fajitas with Cilantro-Lime Cream
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'limes, zested and juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green pepper, sliced vertically'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red pepper, sliced vertically'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'avocado oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, juiced, divided'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': None, 'name': 'flour tortillas, warmed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado - peeled, pitted, and sliced (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pico de gallo, (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'fresh cilantro, chopped (optional)'}
steps: For cilantro-lime cream, place sour cream in a small bowl with a lid. Add cilantro, zest and juice of 2 limes, garlic, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Stir together well, cover, and refrigerate until ready to serve.. For fajita seasoning, combine chili powder, cayenne pepper, cumin, paprika, oregano, salt and pepper in a small bowl; set aside.. In a large bowl or resealable plastic bag, add 2 tablespoons oil, half of lime juice, and fajita seasoning. Stir together or squeeze the bag to combine. Squeeze remaining lime juice over the skillet contents.. Fill warm tortillas with shrimp, peppers, and onions, and garnish with avocado slices, pico de gallo, and additional cilantro, if desired. name: Chipotle-Citrus Marinated Chicken Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'limes, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'orange, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chipotle pepper in adobo'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless skinless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '24', 'unit': None, 'name': 'corn tortilla'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}
steps: Combine lime juice, orange juice, olive oil, chipotle pepper, garlic, cumin, coriander, salt, and black pepper in a blender. Blend on high until smooth.. Pour marinade mixture into a resealable plastic bag. Add chicken breasts to the bag; marinate in the refrigerator for 3 hours.. Preheat a grill to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Place marinated chicken breasts on the grill; close the lid. Discard the marinade. Grill, turning once, until chicken is no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, 6 to 8 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Remove chicken from grill. Let stand for 5 minutes; slice into strips.. Heat tortillas over a griddle on medium heat until tortillas are soft and pliable. Stack tortillas in pairs; divide chicken, onion, and cilantro onto each pair of tortillas.

name: Grilled Chicken Street Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless skinless chicken thighs, trimmed of excess fat'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '24', 'unit': None, 'name': 'corn tortillas (such as'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white onion'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'Mexican hot sauce (such as'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime wedges'}
steps: In a gallon-size resealable bag, place chicken, lime juice, vegetable oil, garlic, cumin, coriander and chili powder. Reseal the bag, and massage bag until chicken is evenly coated. Marinate for 1 to 2 hours in the refrigerator.. Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Remove chicken from marinade and place on the hot grill. Discard marinade. Grill over direct heat until juices run clear, 6 to 8 minutes per side. An instant read thermometer inserted near the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). name: Breakfast Burrito Bowl
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'center-cut bacon'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8-inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'adobo seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'scallions', 'name': 'scallions'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'avocado', 'name': 'avocado'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) for 10 minutes, or according to manufacturer's instructions.. Line the air fryer basket with aluminum foil. Add bacon slices in a single layer and cook until crispy, about 8 minutes.. Remove from the air fryer and set aside on a paper towel-lined plate. Reduce temperature to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Spray 2 large ramekins or heatproof bowls with cooking spray, and press one tortilla inside each bowl with the edges coming up and out.. Crack 2 eggs into each tortilla shell, then top each with 1/4 cup cheese. Sprinkle each with 1/8 teaspoon adobo seasoning and 1/8 teaspoon salt.. Working with one tortilla bowl at a time, cook in the air fryer until tortillas are crispy, egg whites are set, and yolks are runny, 13 to 15 minutes.. While tortillas cook, stir together cherry tomatoes, cilantro, scallions, lime juice, remaining 1/2 teaspoon adobo seasoning, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in a small bowl. Break bacon into small pieces, and set aside.. Remove tortillas from bowls and place on a plate. Top bowls evenly with tomato mixture, avocado, and bacon.

name: Tamales Rojos de Pollo (Red Chicken Tamales)
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'corn husks'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast halves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mulato chiles, stemmed and seeded'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ancho chiles, stemmed and seeded'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cumin seeds'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'boiling water as needed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'masa harina'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Place corn husks in a bowl, cover with boiling water, and soak for a few hours. Drain, place on a work surface, and cover with a clean, damp towel.. Place chicken in a pot, season with salt, and cover with water. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, reduce heat, cover, and simmer until chicken is cooked through, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain chicken and shred with 2 forks.. Heat a griddle over medium heat and toast mulato and ancho chiles until fragrant, 3 to 5 minutes. Place in a bowl and cover with boiling water. Soak until soft, about 25 minutes. Combine ancho and mulato chiles, garlic, cumin seeds, and about 1/2 cup of the soaking water in a blender; blend until a thick, smooth, mole-like sauce forms, adding more water if necessary.. Heat 1 tablespoon lard in a saucepan over medium heat and add the sauce; cook for 3 to 5 minutes. Add shredded chicken and cook until flavors are combined and chicken is heated through, about 5 minutes.. Place remaining lard in a large bowl; beat with an electric mixer until creamy. Add masa harina, chicken broth, baking powder, and 1 1/2 teaspoon salt, and beat until all ingredients are well combined. Test if the masa is ready by dropping a small ball of masa into a glass of cold water; if it floats, it's ready, if not, keep working the dough a little longer.. Select 1 wide corn husk. Spread about 2 tablespoons masa mixture onto the the corn husk, filling it up to 2 inches from the bottom and 1/4 inch from the top. Add 1 tablespoon of the chicken filling in the center of the masa mixture. Fold sides of husk together, one over the other. Fold the bottom of the husk over the seam of the 2 folded sides. Repeat with remaining husks.. Place a steamer insert into a saucepan and fill with water to just below the bottom of the steamer. Bring water to a boil. Add tamales with the open side up and cook until filling is heated through and separates from the husk, about 1 hour. Let tamales rest for 15 minutes before serving.

name: Traditional Mexican Street Tacos

Squeeze lime juice over each taco.

name: Instant Pot Carnitas
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 pound)', 'name': 'pork butt roast'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chile powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'orange juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, coarsely chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, diced, or more to taste'}
steps: Trim excess fat from pork butt; cut pork into 2-inch cubes and transfer to a large bowl.. Combine salt, oregano, cumin, black pepper, chile powder, and paprika in a small bowl. Rub pork cubes with spice mixture. Coat seasoned pork cubes lightly in olive oil; transfer to a pressure cooker. Cover pork cubes with orange juice, onion, and garlic.. Cover pork cubes with orange juice, onion, and garlic.. Place lid on the pressure cooker and lock; bring to full pressure over medium heat until pork is no longer pink in the center, about 60 minutes. Let pressure come down naturally, about 15 minutes.. Remove pork from the pressure cooker and shred meat.

name: Shrimp Quesadillas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'uncooked medium shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapeño pepper, seeded and minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend, divided'}
steps: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and bell peppers; cook, stirring frequently, until onion is translucent and peppers are soft, 6 to 8 minutes. Add salt, cumin, and chili powder; stir to coat vegetables.. Add shrimp; cook and stir until shrimp are opaque and no longer pink in the center, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir in minced jalapeño and lime juice.. Heat another skillet over medium heat and brush with about 1 teaspoon oil. Place one tortilla in the hot skillet; spoon about 1/6 of the shrimp filling and 1/2 cup Mexican cheese blend onto one side of tortilla. Fold tortilla in half. Cook until lightly browned on the bottom, about 5 minutes. Flip and cook until lightly browned on the other side, 3 to 5 minutes. Repeat to make remaining quesadillas.

name: Chilaquiles Rojos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole peeled tomatoes, drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chipotle chiles in adobo sauce, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'white onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'roasted ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'crumbled cotija cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'whole cooked chicken, deboned and shredded'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green onions, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) carton', 'name': 'sour cream, divided'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 10x15-inch casserole dish.. Combine drained tomatoes and chipotle chiles in adobo in a blender; puree until smooth.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion; cook and stir until onion has softened, about 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in garlic until fragrant; add pureed tomato-chile sauce and simmer until mixture starts to thicken. Pour in chicken broth and stir in cumin, oregano, and salt; let simmer until mixture thickens. Remove from heat.. Mix tortilla chips and tomato-chile sauce, folding carefully to cover chips completely. You may have to do this in 2 batches.. Cover the bottom of the casserole dish with half of the tortilla chip mixture. Sprinkle a layer of Mexican cheese and cotija cheese on top. Add shredded chicken to cover all of the cheese. Season chicken with salt and pepper, then sprinkle with 1/2 of the green onions and 1/2 of the cilantro. Spoon 3/4 of the sour cream evenly over top. Spread with the remaining tortilla mixture then top with remaining Mexican and cotija cheeses. Cover with aluminum foil.. Bake in the preheated oven until mixture is bubbly and cheese is melted, 35 to 45 minutes. Remove from the oven and let sit for 5 minutes. Serve with sour cream, green onions, and cilantro.

name: How to Make the Best Conchas, the Most Stunning Mexican Pastry (According to an Expert)
Chef John's Chicken Tinga
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'yellow onion, halved'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'peeled whole garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt, plus more to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(7 ounce) can', 'name': 'chipotle peppers in adobo sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(28 ounce) can', 'name': 'peeled plum tomatoes (preferably San Marzano)'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'crumbled cotija cheese, or to taste'}
steps: Place chicken thighs, chicken stock, water, halved onion, garlic cloves, salt, and oregano in a large pot. Bring to a simmer over high heat; reduce to medium-low and cook, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Remove from heat.. Transfer onion halves to a bowl with a slotted spoon; transfer chicken thighs to a separate bowl.. Pour broth through a strainer into a large bowl.. Heat olive oil in the same pot over medium heat. Add diced onions and cook until beginning to soften, about 4 minutes. Transfer strained liquid to onions. Bring mixture to a boil over high heat; turn heat to medium-low; reduce broth by about half, 15 to 20 minutes.. Transfer reserved boiled onions to a blender. Add chipotle peppers in adobo sauce. Swirl a bit of water in the can and add to the blender. Add tomatoes. Cover blender with the lid; pulse on and off until mixture is partially blended, then blend on medium speed until smooth, 1 or 2 minutes. Transfer to pot with broth and onions.. Increase heat to medium-high. Simmer 15 minutes or so, depending on how thick you want the sauce. Reduce heat to medium-low.. Tear chicken into bite-size pieces and add to the pot. Cook another 10 to 15 minutes. Transfer to a serving dish; garnish with cilantro and crumbled cotija cheese.

name: Chicken Chilaquiles
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'chorizo'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast halves, cut into 1-inch cubes'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(10 ounce) bag', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen corn kernels'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(19 ounce) can', 'name': 'green enchilada sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Monterey Jack cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir chorizo in the hot skillet until crumbly, about 5 minutes. Add chicken; cook and stir until chicken is cooked through and no longer pink in the center, about 10 minutes.. Spread 1/2 of the tortilla chips over the bottom of a casserole dish; top chips with chicken mixture. Sprinkle corn evenly over chicken mixture and layer remaining chips on top. Whisk green enchilada sauce and sour cream in a mixing bowl; pour over chips and top with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.. Bake chilaquiles in the preheated oven until casserole is bubbly and the chips begin to brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
